1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
What if I told you that time can decay?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:10,000
Half-life is the time it takes for half the nuclei in a radioactive sample to decay.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,600
Imagine a clock that counts down, but instead of seconds, it counts down atoms!

4
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:19,600
For example, Carbon-14 has a half-life of about 5,730 years.

5
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:23,600
After this time, half of the original amount has decayed.

6
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:29,200
This decay helps scientists date ancient artifacts and understand the age of our planet.

7
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,800
Want to learn more about the mysteries of science?

8
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,200
Hit follow for more fascinating facts!
